{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#14564: [Vapor] TransitionGroup cannot perform excessive animation on v-if directives",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:15:39.506057+00:00",
  "text": "[Vapor] TransitionGroup cannot perform excessive animation on v-if directives\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.6.0-beta.7\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nClick the 'ToggleShow' button\n\n### What is expected?\n\nAll nodes should enter slowly\n\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nOnly the first node will behave this way\n\n\nAfter clicking twice, the console prints: `Cannot set properties of undefined (setting 'disabled')`\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nI have tried making modifications, but I am not sure if they are correct\n> https://github.com/jackma9604/core/commit/c1f4fd9363e95f4a73b58f3c3772b639edce1e5b",
  "language": "en",
